<p>
<strong>Solves all twenty one cases when given any two inputs. This calcula=
tor calculates for the radius, length, width or chord,=20
height or sagitta, apothem, angle, and area of an arc or circle segment giv=
en any two inputs. Please enter any two values and leave=20
the values to be calculated blank.</strong>=20
There could be more than one solution to a given set of inputs. Please be g=
uided by the angle subtended by the arc. If the angle=20
is greater than 180 degrees then the arc length described is greater than t=
he arc length of a semi-circle=20
(<a href=3D"https://www.handymath.com/calcshtml/arcpics3.html" target=3D"_b=
lank">Click here for illustration</a>). More length units have been added.=
=20
The length unit choices are feet (ft), inch (in), meter (m), centimeter (cm=
), millimeter (mm), yard (yd), kilometer (km),=20
mile (mile). The angle unit choices are degree (deg), radian (rad).
</p></td>
